{{Lunisolar May}} '''May 13''' is the 13th day of month {{ill|May (Lunisolar)|ja|5月 (旧暦)|lt=May|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} the 5th month of the traditional {{ill|Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|ja|旧暦|1=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|11=Japanese Lunisolar Calendar|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} . It's {{ill|Rokuyō|ja|六曜|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} day is {{ill|Taian|ja|大安|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
== Events ==
* {{ill|Kanpyō (era)|ja|寛平|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 ({{ill|Julian calendar|ja|ユリウス暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|889|ja|889th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 14|ja|6月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – Emperor {{ill|Kanmu|ja|桓武天皇|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 's great-grandson, Takamochi-ō, is granted the surname Taira, becoming the ancestor of {{ill|Taira no Masakado|ja|Taira no Masakado|1=Taira no Masakado|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
* {{ill|Ōei (Japan)|ja|Ōei|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 8 (Julian {{ill|1401|ja|1401st year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 24|ja|6月24日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Ashikaga Yoshimitsu|ja|足利義満|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} dispatches an envoy to Ming China, marking the beginning of official Japan-Ming trade relations.
* {{ill|Kanbun (era)|ja|寛文|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12 ({{ill|Gregorian calendar|ja|グレゴリオ暦|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|1672|ja|1672nd year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 8|ja|6月8日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Shōkōkan|ja|彰考館|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} is established at the Mito Domain residence in Koishikawa, advancing the compilation of the {{ill|Dai Nihonshi|ja|大日本史|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} .
* {{ill|Bunsei (era)|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (Gregorian {{ill|1818|ja|1818th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 16|ja|6月16日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – British trader Gordon arrives at {{ill|Uraga, Kanagawa|ja|浦賀|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} seeking trade relations. The {{ill|Tokugawa shogunate|ja|Tokugawa shogunate|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} refuses.
* {{ill|Keiō (Japan)|ja|慶応|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (Gregorian {{ill|1866|ja|1866th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 25|ja|6月25日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The Tokugawa shogunate signs the {{ill|Kaizei Yakusho|ja|改税約書|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Edo Treaty) with Britain, France, the United States, and the Netherlands, lowering import tariffs.
* {{ill|Meiji|ja|明治|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 2 (Gregorian {{ill|1869|ja|1869th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 22|ja|6月22日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Shuppan Jōrei|ja|出版条令|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (Publication Ordinance) is enacted, requiring government approval for publications and establishing the Publishing Investigation Office.
* Meiji 3 (Gregorian {{ill|1870|ja|1870th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 11|ja|6月11日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – The {{ill|Kōgo Jihen|ja|庚午事変|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} occurs.
== Births ==
* {{ill|Kyōwa (Japan)|ja|享和|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 1 (Gregorian {{ill|1801|ja|1801st year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 23|ja|6月23日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Egawa Hidetatsu|ja|江川英龍|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , military scholar and magistrate of Nirayama in Izu Province (+ {{ill|1855|ja|1855th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
== Deaths ==
* {{ill|Bunsei (era)|ja|文政|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} 12 (Gregorian {{ill|1829|ja|1829th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} {{ill|June 14|ja|6月14日|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ) – {{ill|Matsudaira Sadanobu|ja|松平定信|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} , senior councilor (rōjū) of the Tokugawa shogunate and architect of the {{ill|Kansei Reforms|ja|Kanseiの改革|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} (* {{ill|1758|ja|1758th year|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft|12=draft}} ).
== Commemorations ==
* **Bamboo Drunken Day** (竹酔日, *Chikusuibi*) – A Chinese folk belief that this day is the best for transplanting bamboo. It is said that the bamboo is "drunk" and unaware of being moved, allowing it to root well. Also known as **Bamboo Bewilderment Day** (竹迷日), **Dragon Birth Day** (竜生日), or **Bamboo Birth Day** (竹誕日).
---
